The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Satyam net rises 20%

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 Raju: Scaling heights

 Hyderabad, Jan. 20: Satyam Computer Services Ltd has posted a 19.82 per cent rise in net profit at Rs 174.78 crore for the third quarter ended December 31 compared with Rs 145.86 crore in the corresponding previous quarter. Total income has increased to Rs 893.84 crore from Rs 691.14 crore in the year-ago period.

 The group has posted a profit after tax of Rs 164.87 crore for the reporting quarter against Rs 133.48 crore in the same period last year. Total income increased to Rs 909.58 crore from Rs 696.21 crore last year.

 According to the US GAAP, Satyam Computer Services? net income stood at $34.283 million for the quarter under review compared with $28.989 million in the year-ago quarter. Revenues increased to $204.679 million from $148.071 million.

 Talking to reporters after announcing the results today, chairman B. Ramalinga Raju said, ?Our ability to deliver industry-specific solutions and the geographical expansion in Asia and the Pacific region had helped us achieve these scales.?

 The third quarter revenue at Rs 891.26 crore was better than the guidance of Rs 886 crore, while the earnings per share at Rs 5.49 was higher than the expectation of Rs 5.47, he added.

 The revenue from software services grew 5.09 per cent sequentially and 34.5 per cent compared with the last quarter. ?The revenue guidance for this fiscal is expected to be between Rs 3,429 crore and Rs 3,433 crore, indicating a growth of 35.1 per cent,? he said.

 Satyam had added 800 associates during the reporting quarter and brought down the rate of attrition to 15 per cent from 18 per cent in the past, he added. ?We have recruited 3,600 people during this fiscal against a guidance of 4,500 associates.?

 The company has raised the salaries of both offshore and on-shore staff. ?We gave a 40 per cent hike to on-shore and 80 per cent hike to offshore staff,? said Srinivas, Satyam CFO.

 Raju said the company has added 28 new customers, including three Fortune 500 companies, during the quarter. ?We have 350 customers, of which 118 are in the $1-million club.? 

 He said manufacturing, the company?s largest vertical, grew by 9.4 per cent during the quarter.

 Nipuna, the BPO arm of the group, has reported a 255 per cent rise in revenue during the quarter at Rs 12.38 crore. 




